The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes new evaluation schemes and analyzes the performance of different VQA models, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) as it deals with answering questions based on image content.
